               <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1" type="monasticName">ገሪማ፡</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n1" type="normalized">Garimā</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n2" type="baptismalName">ይስሐቅ፡</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n2" type="normalized">Yǝsḥaq</persName>
               <persName><roleName type="title">ʾabbā </roleName></persName>
               <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
               <faith type="EOTC"/>
               <occupation type="ecclesiastic"> saint </occupation>
               <birth> </birth>
               <floruit> He was one of the Nine Saints, a group of foreign monks who arrived in Ethiopia in the 5th and 6th century. He was the son of a king whom he succeeded and 
                  reigned after him for seven years. Then, he recieved a call from ʾabbā <persName ref="PRS7720Pantalew">Ṗanṭalewon</persName> and
                  he left his kingdom and went to <placeName ref="LOC1310Aksum">ʾAksum</placeName>. When the Nine Saints decided to disperse throughout the country, 
                  he went to <placeName ref="LOC4388Madara">Madarā</placeName> where he remianed working miracles.
                  The monastery of  <placeName ref="INS0336EAG">ʾƎndā ʾAbbā Garimā</placeName> is attributed to him.
               </floruit>
               <death ></death>
